english: The community began to follow his guidance.
banjara: apan gor samaj voor vaate saamlen lagpade
notes: apan-our, gor -gor/lambada/banjara, samaj-community, voor-his, vaate-words, saamlen-listening, lagpade-started

english: He became Guru to our people.
banjara: Vuu apner guru er nai vego.
notes: Vuu-he/that person, apner-our, guru  er- teacher/guru, nai-like, vego-became

english: But to fully understand his significance, we must understand where we came from.
banjara: panan apan voor  puuro mahatv samjene, apan vu kattethi aayoch ko bhi dheknu
notes: panan-but, apan-our,  voor-him, puuro-total/full/complete, mahatv-significance/importance, samjene-understand, apan-us, vu-he, kattethi-where, aayoch ko- from came, bhi-also, dheknu-to be seen/ seen.
apner-our, baap-father dada vur- father's, grandfathers's, jaag-place/lang.
aper-our, baap dada vur- fathers' grandfather's, matrubhumi-homeland
